<C>__{schuyler}
<D>__{an iced tea, please }
<A>__{she waves a hand, "yeah, right," without looking back. schuyler sighs and opens the menu. suddenly, someone backhands the side of his skull, he assumes a defensive posture. schuyler sees his laughing brother: david van orton.}
<C>__{david}
<D>__{yo, sky. happy birthday.}
<C>__{schuyler}
<P>__{(rubs his head, annoyed)}
<D>__{thanks, "pee pee." i never get tired of that.}
<A>__{david slides into the seat opposite him. he's in his early 30's, good looking but unkempt, wears bright, funky clothes, an earring and a perpetual grin. there's an intense, edgy quality to him which schuyler has some trouble readjusting to.}
<C>__{schuyler}
<D>__{well... long time.}
